yum install python-pip
pip install py2app
pip uninstall py2app                # <-- you can uninstall

curl -O http://python-distribute.org/distribute_setup.py
python2.7 distribute_setup.py       # Install easy_install module
python2.7 -m easy_install py2app    # <-- for python 2.7
python2.6 distribute_setup.py       # install easy_install module
python2.6 -m easy_install py2app    # <-- for python 2.6

easy_install py2app                 # Install only to LAST distribute_setup.py version !!

To uninstall an .egg you need to 
rm -rf the egg (it might be a directory) 
and remove the matching line from site-packages/easy-install.pth

Q: How to fnd the site-package in use?
$ python 
Python 2.7.5 (default, Jun 27 2013, 13:23:57) 
[GCC 4.4.1 20090725 (Red Hat 4.4.1-2)] on linux2
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
>>> import site; site.getsitepackages()
['/usr/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages', '/usr/local/lib/site-python']

